    25вҶ’## Usage
    27вҶ’### In libraries
    29вҶ’Libraries should link only to the `log` crate, and use the provided macros to
    30вҶ’log whatever information will be useful to downstream consumers:
    31вҶ’
    32вҶ’```toml
    33вҶ’[dependencies]
    34вҶ’log = "0.4"
    35вҶ’```
    36вҶ’
    37вҶ’```rust
    38вҶ’use log::{info, trace, warn};
    39вҶ’
    40вҶ’pub fn shave_the_yak(yak: &mut Yak) {
    41вҶ’    trace!("Commencing yak shaving");
    42вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    58вҶ’### In executables
    60вҶ’In order to produce log output, executables have to use a logger implementation compatible with the facade.
    61вҶ’There are many available implementations to choose from, here are some options:
    62вҶ’
    63вҶ’* Simple minimal loggers:
    64вҶ’    * [`env_logger`](https://docs.rs/env_logger/*/env_logger/)
    65вҶ’    * [`colog`](https://docs.rs/colog/*/colog/)
    66вҶ’    * [`simple_logger`](https://docs.rs/simple_logger/*/simple_logger/)
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   106вҶ’## Structured logging
   108вҶ’If you enable the `kv` feature, you can associate structured data with your log records:
